Manage users and groups
create a group named sharegroup and the following users:
	groupadd sharegroup

haruna with no login shell not a member of sharegroup
	useradd -s /sbin/nologin haruna

umar member of sharegroup
	useradd -G sharegroup umar

adoga with uid 444 member of shregroup
	useradd -u 4444 -G sharegroup adoga

all users should have a password persward
	as root for user in umar adoga haruna;do echo "persward" | passwd --stdin $user; done

change password for adoga to perfect
	passwd adoga perfect


password policies
#enfore password policy to have a min lenght of 8 characters
	vi /etc/security/pwquality.conf
	enable  minlen = 8

set the max password age to 30
	vi /etc/login.defs
	PASS_MAX_DAYS  30 

delete users and groups
remove the user umar from sharegroup
delete the sharegroup
